main event: Two witnesses, Dr. Gordon V. Mohr and his wife, observed a cigar-shaped object with pulsating lights and an orange flame trailing it.
interesting points: The object was larger than a star and had a constant red color.
The object moved in a circular motion at a low altitude.
The sighting lasted for approximately 20 minutes.
There were no sudden changes or accelerations in the object's movement.
The object moved in a slow and erratic motion towards the southwest before disappearing behind trees.
sighted object: cigar-shaped object with pulsating lights and an orange flame
witnesses: Dr. Gordon V. Mohr and his wife
